claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: A screenshot showing the document metadata (Received: 25 April 2023; Accepted: 19 December 2023; Published online: 04 January 2024) with a “Check for updates” prompt and partial, cut-off body text; no visible table data on antigen content or Flublok dosing. does not support the claim because the image contains only header metadata and partial introduction text without any data on hemagglutinin antigen content or comparison of Flublok vs standard-dose vaccines, and thus provides no supporting evidence for the claim.
